comments.body:
I'm not familiar with `@wordpress/components`. Was `isToggled` ever a valid option in this or prior versions of the package? If not, then its probably safe to remove, though I concur with `@p-jackson` it might be worth leaving in with an `@deprecated` pointing to the correct property name. Something like this:

```suggestion
        isPressed?: boolean;
        /** @deprecated Use `isPressed` instead. */
        isToggled?: never;
```
By using `never`, anyone who sets `{ isToggled: true }` would get an error that would lead them to look at the property and ideally see that it is marked as deprecated.

